{"author":{"id":"cc8322a500b8739c77faac347808f6026d9ccb7880d0aaa7ad76754163cd7fdb"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"/R3b+soGGO+Lqt9za2dZPlByY84=","kind":"plan","title":"Slice 5 Reconciliation onto main ŌĆö Implementation Plan"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"S8//5f8JSBTtTCOuJlNLzGx2Bu8=","body":"# Slice 5 Reconciliation onto main ŌĆö Implementation Plan\n\n\u003e **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax.\n\n**Goal:** Land the genuinely-new slice-5 dogfood fixes on top of current `main` (which evolved through hygiene/retier/MCP), reconciling the overlapping link work with main's existing link facet and tier philosophy.\n\n**Context:** `main` advanced far past the old `slice4` base. It already has `Store.AddLink(id, to, linkType string) error` (free-form type, one-directional), a `kref links`/`kref tree` viewer that **computes incoming links by scanning** (so stored inverse links are unnecessary), `kref supersede`, `kref retier`/`promote`/`private` with a `tierRank` (private0\u003cpersonal1\u003cshared2) and a **warn-not-refuse** philosophy for cross-tier links, scan-on-push, and an MCP server. The op-iota ends at `RecordOriginOp = 11`.\n\n**Reconciliation decisions (locked):**\n- Generic link creation: **`kref link add/rm`** (singular verb) beside the existing `kref links` (plural viewer). Reuse main's `Store.AddLink`; **no auto-inverse** (the viewer scans incoming); link **type stays free-form** (default `relates`) to preserve main's `parent-child`/`derived-from`/`tree`.\n- Cross-tier links: **warn, don't refuse** ŌĆö consistent with main's retier. Warn when a link stores a more-private id on a more-public (syncable) source.\n- **Drop** from the original slice-5: the `internal/entry/links.go` vocabulary+inverse, the `LinkOutcome`/auto-inverse `Store.AddLink`, the refuse-based leak guard, and the inline `Links:` line in `kref show` (main's `kref links` covers viewing).\n\n**Tech Stack:** Go, git-bug `entity/dag`, cobra, Ginkgo/Gomega, gitleaks (`internal/scan`).\n\n**Reference (portable code):** the original slice-5 implementation lives on branch `slice5-dogfood-gap-closure`; retrieve any file with `git show slice5-dogfood-gap-closure:\u003cpath\u003e`. The `SetKind`/`AckMerge` ops, `resolve`, `update --file/--kind`, and `ingest --kind` code ports almost verbatim ŌĆö only the link parts are redesigned here.\n\n**Run tests:** `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto KREF_GITLEAKS=/workspace/bin/gitleaks go test ./\u003cpkg\u003e/...` (single pkg) or `task test` / `task test:e2e`. Op-iota note: append new ops at the END of the const block (after `RecordOriginOp`) ŌĆö never mid-block.\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: Entry ops ŌĆö `SetKind` (12) and `AckMerge` (13)\n\n**Files:** `internal/entry/operations.go`, `internal/entry/snapshot.go`, `internal/entry/history.go`, tests in `internal/entry/operations_test.go` (`package entry_test`).\n\nThis is identical to the original slice-5 Tasks 1-2 (no link vocabulary). Retrieve the exact code from `git show slice5-dogfood-gap-closure:internal/entry/operations.go` (the `SetKind` and `AckMerge` types, constructors, `Validate`, `Apply`, and the two unmarshaler cases) and the `AckedMerges []string json:\"-\"` field on `Snapshot`, and the `set-kind`/`ack-merge` history mappings.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write failing tests** ŌĆö port the `SetKind` and `AckMerge` Describe blocks from `git show slice5-dogfood-gap-closure:internal/entry/operations_test.go`, and extend the \"maps every op type\" test in `history_test.go` to append `NewSetKind(author,\"memory\")` and `NewAckMerge(author,[]string{\"h\"})` with `\"set-kind\"`, `\"ack-merge\"` added to the expected slice.\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run, confirm fail** ŌĆö `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/entry/...` ŌåÆ undefined `NewSetKind`.\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement** ŌĆö append `SetKindOp`, `AckMergeOp` at the END of the iota; add both op types (verbatim from the slice5 branch), unmarshaler cases, `Snapshot.AckedMerges` (`json:\"-\"`), and the two history mappings. Do NOT create `internal/entry/links.go`.\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run, confirm pass** ŌĆö `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/entry/...` ŌåÆ ok.\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit** ŌĆö `git add internal/entry/{operations,snapshot,history}.go internal/entry/{operations,history}_test.go \u0026\u0026 git commit -m \"feat(entry): add SetKind and AckMerge operations\"` (append the `Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e` trailer; same for every commit below).\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: Store ŌĆö SetKind, clearable merge, RemoveLink, leak query\n\n**Files:** `internal/store/store.go` (and a new method near the link/`AddLink` code in `internal/store/hygiene.go`), tests in `internal/store/store_test.go`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write failing tests**\n  - `SetKind`: add an entry, `s.SetKind(id,\"spec\")`, assert `Get(id).Kind==\"spec\"`.\n  - Clearable merge: port the two-store divergence + ack test from `git show slice5-dogfood-gap-closure:internal/store/store_test.go` (the \"clears the flag after kref resolve\" and cross-machine ack cases). The existing main test asserting `Merged==true` after divergence must still pass.\n  - `RemoveLink`: `s.AddLink(a, b.String(), \"relates\")`, then `s.RemoveLink(a, b.String())`, assert `Get(a).Links` empty.\n  - `LinkWouldLeak`: a `shared` source linking a `private` target ŌåÆ true; same-tier ŌåÆ false; `private`ŌåÆ`shared` ŌåÆ false.\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run, confirm fail.**\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement**\n  - `Store.SetKind(id, kind)` ŌĆö mirror `SetStatus` (all-tier search, append `entry.NewSetKind`).\n  - Reframe merge detection (port from slice5): add `mergeCommits(id) ([]string, error)` (the `\u003e1 parent` walk, hashes as `string(h)`), `UnacknowledgedMerge(snap *entry.Snapshot) (bool,error)` (uses `snap.AckedMerges`), keep `Merged(id)` as a wrapper (`Get` then `UnacknowledgedMerge`), and `AcknowledgeMerge(id) (int,error)` (appends `entry.NewAckMerge(fresh)`; returns 0 when nothing unacknowledged). Replace main's old standalone `Merged` walk body with `mergeCommits`.\n  - `Store.RemoveLink(id entity.Id, to string) error` ŌĆö mirror main's `AddLink` in `hygiene.go` (all-tier search, append `entry.NewRemoveLink(s.author, to)`).\n  - `Store.LinkWouldLeak(from, to entity.Id) (bool, error)` ŌĆö `Get` both, return `tierRank(toTier) \u003c tierRank(fromTier)` (reuse the existing unexported `tierRank` in `retier.go`; both files are `package store`). Document: \"true when the link stores a more-private id on a more-public (syncable) source ŌĆö the caller warns and proceeds.\"\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run, confirm pass** ŌĆö `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto KREF_GITLEAKS=/workspace/bin/gitleaks go test ./internal/store/...` (full suite, incl. main's existing retier/hygiene/pushed specs).\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit** ŌĆö `feat(store): SetKind, clearable merge (resolve), RemoveLink, LinkWouldLeak`.\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: Bridge ŌĆö export `SplitMarker`, thread `kind`\n\n**Files:** `internal/bridge/bridge.go`, callers (`internal/bridge/bridge_test.go`, `internal/bridge/marker_test.go`, `cmd/kref/commands.go`'s `newIngestCmd`).\n\nPort the reconciled (final) slice-5 bridge behavior ŌĆö including the fix that a **kind-less** ingest preserves an existing entry's kind. Retrieve from `git show slice5-dogfood-gap-closure:internal/bridge/bridge.go`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write failing tests** ŌĆö port the \"Ingest kind\" tests: kind on create; re-ingest with a different kind re-kinds; **re-ingest with `kind==\"\"` leaves the stored kind untouched**; bare-create (`\"\"`) yields `document`. Update all existing `Ingest(...)`/`IngestPaths(...)` calls in the bridge tests to the new signatures.\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run, confirm fail.**\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement** ŌĆö rename `splitMarker`ŌåÆ`SplitMarker` (update `IDFromFile`, `Ingest` callers); `Ingest(s, path, tier, kind, actor, actorKind)` where `kind==\"\"` means unspecified (create ŌåÆ `document`; re-ingest ŌåÆ leave kind, only `SetKind` when `kind != \"\" \u0026\u0026 kind != existing.Kind`); `IngestPaths(..., kind, ...)`. In `newIngestCmd`, add `--kind` (default `document` for help) but pass `\"\"` unless `cmd.Flags().Changed(\"kind\")`, and call `bridge.IngestPaths(s, args, t, k, skipMissing, actor, actorKind)`.\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run, confirm pass** ŌĆö `go test ./internal/bridge/... ./cmd/...`.\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit** ŌĆö `feat(ingest): --kind (kind-less ingest preserves kind); export SplitMarker`.\n\n---\n\n## Task 4: Render ŌĆö reword the merged string\n\n**Files:** `internal/render/render.go`, `internal/render/render_test.go`.\n\nDo **not** add an inline `Links:` line to `Show` (main's `kref links` is the viewer). Only reword the merged flag.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write/adjust test** ŌĆö assert `Show` output for a merged snapshot contains `clear with `kref resolve``.\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run, confirm fail.**\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement** ŌĆö change the merged line in `Show` to `ŌŚå merged ŌĆö concurrent edits auto-merged; review with `kref diff`, clear with `kref resolve``. If a main test pins the old string, update it.\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run, confirm pass** ŌĆö `go test ./internal/render/...`.\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit** ŌĆö `feat(render): point the merged flag at kref resolve`.\n\n---\n\n## Task 5: CLI ŌĆö update rework, resolve, link add/rm, ingest --kind\n\n**Files:** `cmd/kref/commands.go`, `cmd/kref/main.go`, `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write failing tests**\n  - `update`: title-only rename; kind-only; `--file` override (trailer stripped); `--body`+`--file` conflict errors; no-mutation+empty-stdin errors; `--file` secret on a syncable entry fails closed; update via path selector. (Port from `git show slice5-dogfood-gap-closure:cmd/kref/cli_test.go`.)\n  - `resolve`: no-op prints \"nothing to resolve\"; JSON status `nothing-to-resolve` when n==0.\n  - `link`: `kref link add A B --type depends-on` (both shared) then `kref links A` shows the link; `kref link rm A B`; `kref link add \u003cshared\u003e \u003cprivate\u003e` **warns** (stderr contains \"warn\"/\"private\") and **succeeds** (exit 0).\n  - `ingest --kind`: ingest a file `--kind spec`, assert `list --kind spec` finds it.\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run, confirm fail.**\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement**\n  - Replace `newUpdateCmd` with the slice-5 reworked version (port from the slice5 branch): `--body`/`--file`/`--title`/`--kind`, body-source precedence (`--body` XOR `--file` XOR stdin), `resolveArg` path selector, title/kind-only, and `--file` secret scan (fail-closed on a non-private entry, allowed on private). Add `import internal/scan`.\n  - Add `newResolveCmd` (`kref resolve \u003cid|path\u003e` ŌåÆ `s.AcknowledgeMerge`; `nothing-to-resolve` JSON status when n==0); register in `main.go` lifecycle group.\n  - Add `newLinkCmd` (`kref link add|rm`):\n    - `add \u003cid|path\u003e \u003ctarget\u003e [--type relates]`: resolve both via `resolveArg`; `if leak,_ := s.LinkWouldLeak(from,to); leak { print a stderr warning that a more-private id rides along on push, then proceed }`; `s.AddLink(from, to.String(), linkType)`; emit a \"linked\" confirmation (human + JSON `{status, from, to, type, cross_tier_warning}`).\n    - `rm \u003cid|path\u003e \u003ctarget\u003e`: `s.RemoveLink(from, to.String())`; emit \"unlinked\".\n    - Register in `main.go` core group (after `newLinksCmd`).\n  - `ingest --kind`: ensure the flag from Task 3 is wired (default `document`, passed only when Changed).\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run, confirm pass** ŌĆö `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto KREF_GITLEAKS=/workspace/bin/gitleaks go test ./cmd/...`.\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit** ŌĆö `feat(cli): update --file/--kind, kref resolve, kref link add/rm, ingest --kind`.\n\n---\n\n## Task 6: Docs ŌĆö README + CHANGELOG\n\n**Files:** `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Update README**\n  - Command reference: `kref update \u003cid|path\u003e [--body --file --title --kind]`, `kref link add|rm \u003cid|path\u003e \u003ctarget\u003e [--type]`, `kref resolve \u003cid|path\u003e`, `kref ingest \u003cpath\u003e... [--kind --tier --skip-missing]`.\n  - History \u0026 divergence: replace \"review `kref log`, then `kref edit` to settle\" with the `kref resolve` clearable-flag flow (and the concurrent-ack self-heal note).\n  - Links: under Hygiene/links, add that `kref link add|rm` creates/removes generic typed links (free-form `--type`, default `relates`), complementing `kref links`/`tree`/`supersede`; cross-tier links to a more-private entry **warn** (the id rides along on push) but proceed ŌĆö consistent with `retier`.\n  - Note `update --file` and `ingest` (file-sourced) are gitleaks-scanned; `--body`/stdin are not. Note a kind-less ingest preserves an existing kind (hook-safe).\n- [ ] **Step 2: Update CHANGELOG** ŌĆö under `[Unreleased] Added`: clearable `ŌŚå merged` via `kref resolve` (`AckMerge` op); `kref link add/rm` (generic typed links; cross-tier warn); `kref update --file/--kind`, path selector, title/kind-only; `kref ingest --kind` (kind-less preserves).\n- [ ] **Step 3: Verify docs vs reality** ŌĆö `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto task build \u0026\u0026 ./bin/kref update --help \u0026\u0026 ./bin/kref link add --help \u0026\u0026 ./bin/kref resolve --help \u0026\u0026 ./bin/kref ingest --help`.\n- [ ] **Step 4: Commit** ŌĆö `docs: document kref resolve, link add/rm, update --file/--kind, ingest --kind`.\n\n---\n\n## Final verification\n- [ ] `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto task check` (fmt + lint + unit + e2e) green.\n- [ ] Smoke against the real binary: title/kind-only update; `kref link add` same-tier + cross-tier-warn; `kref resolve` clears `ŌŚå merged` after a two-clone divergence; `ingest --kind`; confirm main's existing verbs (`links`, `tree`, `supersede`, `retier`, `promote`, MCP) still work.\n\n## Self-review (planning)\n- Spec coverage: net-new (resolve/merged, update --file/--kind, ingest --kind) ŌåÆ Tasks 1-5; reconciled links (kref link add/rm, warn) ŌåÆ Tasks 2,5; docs ŌåÆ Task 6.\n- Dropped vs original slice-5 (deliberate): links vocabulary/inverse, refuse-guard, inline Links-in-show ŌĆö superseded by main's link facet + warn philosophy.\n- Names used consistently: `SetKind`/`AckMerge`/`AckedMerges`/`UnacknowledgedMerge`/`mergeCommits`/`AcknowledgeMerge`/`RemoveLink`/`LinkWouldLeak`/`SplitMarker`. main's `AddLink(id, to string, type)` reused unchanged (MCP/supersede unaffected)."}]}